A unique "electronic goods ticket" for return items Setouchi City added with hometown tax: Sanyo Shimbun Digital|san Digi
Electronic gift ticket "e-city gift."
i'll contact the dedicated device and settle it.
On the 27th, Setouchi City announced that it would add its own electronic ticket "emachi Gift" to the return items of the hometown tax.
It is available in the city's affiliated stores from November.
It is the first municipality in the prefecture.
If you pay a home tax and choose an electronic goods ticket as a return item, it will be sent to a designated smartphone with a donation equivalent to 30%.
At the time of purchase, the shop will show the screen of the ticket, and the store will contact the stamp-type special equipment to settle it.
They cannot sell or sell.
Return items usually require a certain amount of time from application to arrival, but electronic ticketing can be received instantly.
Tourists can use it easily.
In addition to the five hometown tax portal sites, it is also accepted on two special sites in the city.
The current membership is 13 stores and aims to reach 100 by the end of this fiscal year.
In June, the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications established a new system to regulate local products in order to prevent excessive competition among municipalities, with the amount of return products raised by 30% or less of donations.
"The city plans to become a member of a local product company, and within the guidelines."
In the 18th fiscal year of Setouchi City, the amount of hometown tax is about 430 million yen.
