Driving at high heels is dangerous!
Accidents involving young people mistake pedals - Yahoo! News
Violation of road traffic laws
However, it is a big mistake to think that it is only an elderly driver.
According to the 2015 National Police Agency data, more than 1080 cases were in the age of 24 or younger, exceeding 1032 cases over 75 years of age.
It is important to call attention to young people as well as to the elderly.
do you take your feet?
is it safe?
There is no description of gender ratio or cause of this data, but unlike the elderly, which is often thought to be due to the decline of the body, such as driving skills and reflexes, there is a possibility that the young age group may be misled by other things such as music and conversation, or trampled due to clothes.
In particular, some women choose high heels, pamps, sandals, and mulles and choose various shoes according to their clothes that day and drive them as they are.
While some people know that it is not suitable for driving, it is troublesome to change clothes, but some people do not think of the possibility that it will lead to danger at all, and many people are driving without hesitation.
However, driving on high heels and sandals violates road traffic laws.
One is to ensure the operation of the steering wheel, brakes, and other operations, and Article 70 "Prohibition of safety driving obligations" which stipulates that the operation should not be carried out to cause accidents and harm people.
The other is Article 71, which stipulates that the driver must comply with the matters stipulated by the prefectural public safety committee, for example, in Article 12 of the Miyazaki Prefectural Road Traffic Law Enforcement Regulations, "Don't drive a vehicle (except light vehicles) by wearing shoes in a manner that prevents or hinders driving operations, such as wearing shoes, slippers, high heels, etc.
The aim of each prefecture is to consider driving in " footwear that may interfere with driving operation" even if not specified as high heels.
So why is driving at high heels dangerous?
It is obvious to consider the basics of pedaling safely.
For safe and secure pedal operation, first place the foot to the floor, put the foot to be perpendicular to the brake pedal, and then tilt the foot to the right as a starting point when stepping on the accelerator pedal.
At this time, it is important to keep the car firmly fixed so that it does not break regardless of the car's behavior.
However, in high heels, the area where the kakato is grounded on the floor is small, and the area of the foot which is grounded on the pedal is smaller and the area of the foot that is grounded on the pedal is difficult to adjust.
This may lead to danger.
In addition, most cars have floor carpets, but this material is easy to get rid of the high heels, and when it comes to emergency braking, the heels are pulled and the pedals cannot be trampled, or the heels are removed from the beats that are pulled, and the heels are stuck in the back of the pedals and cannot be stepped.
In addition, there are cases where the heel is pulled to the back of the pedal when the pedal is pushed back and the accelerator pedal is no longer returned.
Toyota and Subaru Accelerate Joint Development (Response) - Yahoo! News
Toyota and Subaru agreed on a new business capital alliance on September 27.
Toyota acquires additional Subaru shares and becomes an affiliate of equity law.
Since the agreement in 2005, the two companies have been working together to produce Toyota vehicles, supply vehicles from Toyota to Subaru, and jointly develop the FR sports car 86.
In June this year, we agreed to develop EV-only platforms and EV vehicles using Subaru's AWD technology and Toyota's electrification technology.
In this agreement, Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares.
At present, Subaru shares held by Toyota have a voting ratio of 16.83%.
The company is a subsidiary of Toyota Corporation.
On the other hand, Subaru acquires Toyota shares, equivalent to the amount equivalent to the amount required by Toyota to acquire Subaru shares (up to 8 billion yen).
The two companies will develop and strengthen cooperation through business capital alliances.
Joint development of the AWD and 86/BRZ models, expansion of THS (Toyota Hybrid System) for Subaru vehicles, cooperation in the connectivity field, and technical cooperation in the autonomous driving field.
United States, at the lowest level of refugee acceptance for three consecutive years, 18,000 | Shizuoka Shimbun
The U.S. Department of State announced on October 26, 2020 that it would reduce the number of refugees receiving from around the world to 18,000.
The minimum number of refugees since 1980 has been renewed for three consecutive years.
The Trump administration aims to appeal to the conservatives to strict immigration and refugee policies in line with the presidential election next year.
It is imperative that human rights groups and other organizations criticize each other as there are no people who are expelled from the country in various places.
The previous Obama administration set the upper limit of the 17th fiscal year to 110,000, but the Trump administration, which was launched in January 17th, reversed this and reduced it to 50,000.
In the 18th fiscal year, the number has decreased to 45,000 and in the 19th fiscal year to 30,000.
