Korea-Bulgarian Summit Meeting - Yahoo! News
(SEOUL=Yonhap News) South Korea's President Moon Jae-in met with Bulgaria's Prime Minister Borisov during his official visit to Korea on July 27 to discuss the substantial expansion of cooperation between the two countries.
The Prime Minister of Bulgaria visited Korea for the first time.
President Moon welcomed the visit to Korea before the 30th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations next year and appreciated the leadership of Prime Minister Borisov, who led the development of Bulgaria.
The two leaders appreciated the continued increase in trade and investment between the two countries amid the growing global protectionism and agreed to work together to expand economic cooperation in the future.
President Moon welcomed Bulgaria's policy to grant Korean companies the status of "strategic investors" and expressed his hope that Korean companies will invest in Bulgaria based on this.
He also stressed that while Bulgaria is promoting the introduction of nuclear power and modernization of national defense, Korea will be the best partner for Bulgaria, and called for attention and cooperation to enable Korean companies to participate in the order of the Bulgarian government's nuclear power plants and the promotion of the defense industry.
The two leaders also agreed to strengthen future-oriented cooperation in the battery and automotive parts sectors of electric vehicles and renewable energy.
Prime Minister Borisov hoped that close cooperation will be carried out in the fields of ICT (information and communication technology) and science and technology as well as education.
He also spoke about the Korean Peninsula's peace process, and expressed his gratitude for the support of the Korean government's efforts toward peace consolidation on the Korean Peninsula, including the announcement of Bulgaria's support for the North-South and North-South Summit.
Prime Minister Borisov appreciated the will of the President of the Republic of Korea and the efforts of the Korean government to build a peace regime on the Korean Peninsula, and reiterated his firm support for the Bulgarian government.
The meeting was attended by Mr. Song Yunmo, Secretary of the Ministry of Trade, Industry and Energy, Mr. Lee Houn, Secretary of the Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry, and Mr. Kim Hyun-jong, Second Secretary of the National Security Office.
As the deputy director of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Kang Gyeongfa, who was visiting the U.S., also attended the First Secretary of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs Zhao Seyong.
Local Industry in Hyogo-Awaji Island, Kinki Ceramics Co., Ltd., manufactured by "Awaji Kawara" filed for quasi-self bankruptcy debt of approximately 2 billion yen (Imperial Data Bank) - Yahoo!
It was also affected by the sluggish housing market and the increasing number of damage caused by the earthquake that caused "consumer roofing."
Kinki Ceramics Co., Ltd. (TDB Code: 530173983, Capital: 99.2 million yen, Otani 881-8, Awaji City, Hyogo Prefecture, Representative Yukizo Fukuhara, and 44 employees) filed for quasi-self bankruptcy at the Kobe District Court on August 30.
The application representative was Daichi Yoshida (1-10-8 Nishitenman, Kita Ward, Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture), Daichi Yoshida Law Office and Telephone 06-665-6038.
The company was founded in June 1895 and reorganized in April 1961.
At first, he started his business as Ibushi tile maker, a local industry in Awaji Island, in Nishitan-cho, Mihara County (present-day Minamiawaji City).
In October 1986, Kyowa Kiln Co., Ltd. merged with Kyowa Kiln Co., Ltd. and succeeded the business of Kinki Sangyo Co., Ltd., while at the same time changing its current business name and moving its head office to its present location.
After that, sales offices were established in Fukuyama City, Hiroshima City, Oita City, Miyazaki City, etc., and it became the current system.
In the fiscal year ended December 2004, sales of approximately 3116 million yen were recorded.
He was well known as the top tile maker of Awaji Island.
However, due to the sluggish housing market since the Lehman shock and the repeated damage caused by the Great East Japan Earthquake and the Kumamoto Earthquake, the demand for the roof of the roof of the roof of the roof of the consumer was sluggish, and the annual sales for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2018 fell to approximately 134 million yen.
In terms of revenue, the profit margin was declining due to the surge in fuel prices, as well as a continuous deficit with excessive interest-bearing debt associated with inventory burdens and business fixed investment.
For this reason, although financial institutions were trying to rebuild their business by requesting financial institutions to ease the repayment conditions for their borrowings, there was no signs of recovery in business conditions, and the financial position gradually became tight.
I couldn't help but quit the business and took this action.
The debt is currently under investigation, but it is estimated to be about 20 billion yen.
Prefectural Dinosaur Museum in Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture, which promotes "industrialization of tourism" (photo taken with Japanese aerial photographs and small unmanned drones)
Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture announced on September 25 that it would acquire approximately 25,000 square meters of land adjacent to the construction site of the road station "Dinosaur Valley Katsuyama," which opened next spring.
To accelerate the "industrialization of tourism" advocated by the city and the local economy, we aim to attract hotels and restaurants specializing in accommodation.
The Board of Directors explained the same day at the Special Committee on the Establishment of the City Council's Guest Center.
With the opening of the Hokuriku Shinkansen in the spring of 2023, as well as the opening of the entire section of Chubu Ritsukan Expressway in the prefecture, the expansion of the prefectural Dinosaur Museum (Katsuyama City) and enhancement of functions, the city plans to move from day trip center to stay-type sightseeing and attract accommodation.
To get it, a private vacation place next to the road station construction site east.
Surrounded by Kuzuryu-gawa River, Takinami-gawa River, and prefectural roads, it is twice the size of a roadside station (about 12,000 square meters).
Under the name of industrial complex development, the City Land Development Corporation will negotiate land from this fiscal year and build land in FY21 after acquiring land.
According to the city, private businesses such as farmers' restaurants and harvest experience facilities, fast food, and restaurants already have a chance to expand their business.
As for accommodation, it was also revealed that Sekisui House has raised its name as a city to attract accommodation-specific hotels adjacent to roadside stations planned nationwide.
The company plans to expand into three locations in Fukui Prefecture, but it is also possible that multiple cities will attract and compete.
The city plans to build a parking lot.
Some members said that the maintenance schedule was slow, and asked for speeding up, and others said, "Don't have the land to sleep."
Mr. Minoru Mizukami, deputy mayor of the city, stated that he would like to promote the superiority of Katsuyama City by focusing on the Prefectural Dinosaur Museum and Ski Jam Katsuyama.
