BITPoint, which leaked crypto assets worth 30 billion yen, resumed service (Gunfusha Gold Online) - Yahoo! News
In July of this year, crypto asset exchanges, which amounted to 30 billion yen, such as bitcoin, were illegally leaked.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., the operator, announced on September 30 that it would resume sending crypto assets.
There seems to be a certain point, including measures to prevent recurrence.
BITPoint leaked Bitcoin and Ripple this July.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., which operates Crypto Asset Exchange BITPoint, announced on September 27 that it will resume its services around 14:00 on Monday, September 30.
In addition to responding to customers who suffered damage and communicating with the Financial Services Agency, there seems to have been a certain point, including measures to prevent recurrence, such as the management system including security aspects.
Bitpoint Japan said, "We will resume our services as soon as possible, with safety first, and strive to recover the credit from users."
In July of this year, the exchange launched a crypto asset fraud incident worth 3 billion yen, including Bitcoin and Ripple.
At the press conference after that, regarding the continuation of the business, he mentioned, "Even if the compensation amount is deducted, the current account balance is about 30 billion yen."
