<One year from the Eastern Iburi Earthquake> Water Supply at the time of power outage"Smoking plug" will be installed directly connected to the water pipe Hakodate Mansion: Hokkaido Shimbun
In response to the blackout caused by the Eastern Iburi Earthquake in September last year, measures have been taken in condominiums in Hakodate City where water was cut off.
According to the City Bureau of Enterprises, seven condominiums were installed in one year after the earthquake, and a "watering plug" was installed that could produce water even after power outages.
There are about 400 condominiums and private residences in the city that provide water with a "passenger tank" that can be watered at the time of power outage.
The house's water supply system is roughly divided into two types: the "passenger tank type" that is used to feed water into the water tank once underground or on the roof, and the "direct connection type" that directly feeds water from the city's water supply pipe to each door.
Even if the water pipe is not damaged, the electric pumps that pump water from the water tank to each door will not move due to power failure, so the water supply will not be able to be provided and each door will be dehydrated.
Training (Aomori Broadcasting) - Yahoo!
A training session was held in Shingo Village to search and rescue people who had suffered before the autumn mushroom harvest season.
60 people participated in the training at Hirakozawa Forest Park in Shingo Village, including police and firefighters and hunter-gatherers.
At the opening ceremony, Chief Tsukuda of the Goto Police Department called for close cooperation and training.
★ Takahashi Regional Manager's declaration "We will start mountain training and rescue training."
The training was carried out with the assumption that a man who went out to see the mushroom harvest would not return home at night.
The participants are divided into three groups and search through the mountains with the names of missing men.
In Shingo Village, a 70-year-old man who entered the mountain in June was missing and rescued the next day after being injured.
We found a man who was injured in the training and confirmed the cooperation between search and rescue on the carrier and prepared for the autumn mushroom harvest season, which is prone to distress.
