Tokai-mura critical accident, 20 years in 30 days, 300 nuclear facility troubles: Hokkaido Shimbun
From fiscal 2000 to fiscal 2006 after the critical accident in Tokai-mura, Ibaraki Prefecture, which was the first time in Japan's history of nuclear power, 336 incidents of accidents and failures occurred at nuclear facilities across Japan were reported.
20 years in 30 days from a critical accident that alarmed the safety myth of the nuclear industry.
The report covers about 90% of the international assessment measures (INES) that show seriousness (not important for safety) and those that are not evaluated.However, due to the lessons learned from the accident and the accident at the Fukushima Daiichi Nuclear Power Plant in Tokyo Electric Power Co., Ltd. in 11 years, there is a need to raise awareness of safety.
