New charges for mobile phones Price reduction in fair competition: Hokkaido Shimbun
A new fee plan for a mobile phone company was released as a result of the revision of the Telecommunications Business Law in October.
However, it generally stopped high.
Chief Cabinet Secretary Yoshihide Suga said last summer, "There is room for a reduction of about 40 percent," and despite the high expectations for price reduction, there was no price competition.
It is a major factor that the full-scale entry into Rakuten was postponed and the oligorization of three major companies continued.
It is desirable for consumers to have a fair competition that makes them easy to use.
I want to ask for the efforts of mobile companies.
The amendment prohibits a set discount for terminal and communication charges.
Instead of selling the terminal fee, the communication fee was set to increase.
SoftBank and KDDI (au) announced plans to make the device up to half the price.
However, both companies can't use other companies' lines for 100 days.
NTT DOCOMO makes up to one third of the terminal fee for only subscribers of its own line.
The three companies continue to "enclosure" to prevent transfers to other companies.
As for SIM locking, the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications announced that it would require immediate cancellation.
Companies need to respond quickly.
Rakuten's postponement was due to the lack of improvement of communication networks such as base stations as planned.
It was expected to be a detonator of lower price competition, so it looked like a shoulder.
I wonder if there was a sweetness of the outlook.
The start and rate of full-scale services are not disclosed.
As a company that plays a role in social infrastructure, I would like to take responsibility for the business.
This time, the price revision was triggered by the remarks of Chief Cabinet Secretary Suga.
Mr. Suga expressed his dissatisfaction with the new charges of the three companies, saying, "I think competition will start from now on, and I don't think it's going to be okay."
However, the reduction in government-made prices does not seem to distort the market and encourage healthy competition.
The company should develop customer-oriented competition before it is announced by the government.
The cost system of each company is very complex and not easy to compare.
The Consumer Affairs Agency called attention to the fact that while the terminal advertises such as "maximum half price," there are cases where the consumer burden exceeds half price.
In order to avoid misunderstandings of users by the company itself, it is necessary to make careful and easy-to-understand explanations.
Reduced withdrawal limit to 500,000 yen Cash card of 3 Shinkin in Mie Prefecture - Ise Shimbun
Three Shinkin Banks in Mie Prefecture (Kuwana Mie Shinkin Bank, Kita Ise Kozuke Shinkin Bank, and Kihoku Shinkin Bank) announced on June 26 that they decided to reduce the amount of withdrawals by cash cards to prevent damage to special scams.
In the past three years, the bank holds cash cards from three banks: Kuwana Mie, Kita Ise Ueno, and Kihoku, with a maximum amount of 500,000 yen per day for depositors over 70 years old who have never made a certain amount of withdrawal transactions at ATMs.
The Kuwana Mie Shinkin Bank and Kita Ise Ueno Shinkin Bank will be lowered on October 1, and the Kihoku Shinkin Bank will be lowered from November 1.
In the prefecture, there are many special fraud cases in which cash cards and PINs are stolen by ATMs, such as financial institutions and police officials, and those involved in the Shinkin Bank say "I want to protect your important deposits in the manner possible."
