On September 26, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare (MHLW) announced the first name of 424 hospitals in 1455 public hospitals and public hospitals in Japan, which judged that their medical records were poor.
In Fukui Prefecture, the Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare reviewed the results of the treatment of 14 public and public hospitals, and four facilities were targeted: Awara Hospital, the National Hospital Organization of Wara City, and Awara Hospital, the Three Kingdoms Hospital of Wicked Echizen-cho Oda Hospital, the Wakasa Takahama Hospital of Wicked Takahama-cho.
⇒ 4 hospitals to be reorganized "Standard Funny"
In order to prevent the expansion of medical expenses due to the aging of the population, it was necessary to promote reorganization and integration with hospitals in competing regions.
In October, we would like to request a full-scale review of reorganization and integration at the target hospital, and conclude by September next year.
There is no compulsion force, but it is expected that the local chiefs and residents will be repulsed due to fears that close hospitals will disappear.
It was announced at the meeting the same day.
The total hospital was 29.1%, with relatively few beds.
By prefecture, Niigata (53, 7 percent), Hokkaido (48, 6 percent), Miyagi (47, 5 percent), Yamaguchi (46, 7 percent) and Okayama (43, 3 percent).
The number of targets was 54 in Hokkaido, and Okinawa was the only zero.
Based on data from FY2017, the Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare conducted a survey of 1455 hospitals in public and public hospitals that respond to "altitude acute phase" for severe patients and "acute phase" for general surgery.
He analyzed nine medical records, including cancer and emergency medicine, and whether the competing hospitals were located within 20 minutes by car.
The target hospital will be considered to be abolished and some medical departments will be transferred to other hospitals.
Medical expenses increased rapidly in 25 years, when all the baby boomers were 75 or older.
For this reason, the Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare has set a goal of reducing the number of hospital beds to 19.11,000 beds in 18 years.
Currently, there are many beds in the "altitude acute phase" and "acute phase" where nurses are carefully placed and medical expenses are paid, but there is a shortage of rehabilitation services that are highly needed for elderly people.
In order to cope with aging, it is necessary not only to reduce the number of beds but also to increase rehabilitation.
For the reorganization and integration of hospitals, each prefecture formulated a "regional medical concept" that defined the number of beds required for 25 years.
Although the country is divided into 339 districts, local governments and medical officials discuss it, many local residents and chiefs maintain a cautious attitude and the debate is difficult.
The Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare wants to revitalize the discussion by publishing the names of hospitals with poor results.
Comprehensive training for disaster prevention, such as the assumption of eruption of Mt.Komagatake, road etc.
On September 27th, a comprehensive disaster prevention drill was held in the forests, Nanae, and Kabe-cho in the Watari Island tube.
About 400 people from 20 organizations including roads and 3 towns participated.
The first event since the Hokkaido Komagatake Volcano Disaster Prevention Council formulated an evacuation plan incorporating evacuation routes for residents in August.
It was the first time in 18 years that local residents participated in the extensive training.
At 8:45 a.m., Mt.Komake erupted and mud flow reached the town at the foot of the mountain.
When the eruption warning level was raised to 5 (evacuation), shelters were opened in both Mori and Nanae towns, and residents moved by buses and police cars prepared by each town.
