About 100,000 citizens, mainly students, sympathized with 16-year-old environmental activist Greta Tunberg, marched in Vancouver on September 27 to protest climate change.
Climate demonstrations in Vancouver
The march took place from Vancouver City Hall to Canby Bridge and to downtown libraries.
In front of the city hall of the meeting place, people with placards began to gather for hours before the start, and at 13 o'clock at the start time, the number of people to fill the road of the city hall's front block.
