500 portable translators completed installation Free loan to Hamamatsu Chamber of Commerce and shops | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
PokeTalk, a portable translation machine that provides free loan to 500 stores in Hamamatsu City.
On June 26, the Hamamatsu Chamber of Commerce and Industry announced that it had completed the installation of 500 portable translation machines at its member offices, including stores in Hamamatsu.
It is the first time in Japan to deploy this translator in a concentrated manner in the same region, and it is attracting attention whether it will improve the ability to respond to inbound tourists.
The loan includes 236 restaurants, 113 retail stores, 17 accommodations, and 134 others.
The city has 60% of its population.
We started to show where to rent Google Map, a map app, so we could see the location of a foreign language store on a smartphone.
It is accessible from the Hamana Lake Tourism Area website.
The free loan of PokeTalk, which corresponds to 74 languages, was initiated in April by nine organizations in the city under the declaration of Hamamatsu, Japan's largest inbound support city.
The Chamber of Commerce will purchase 500 units and lend them to small and medium-sized businesses that meet the requirements of obtaining hospitality certification and introducing cashless payments.
The representative of the Chamber of Commerce said, "We want to help foreign customers develop new customers while the business environment is severe."
