First Ice (Gifu Shimbun Web) - Yahoo! News
Ice observed for the first time in this season at Tsurugaike Pond in Norikura-dake tatami maturation: Tanseigawa-cho, Takayama City (Provided by Norikura Skyline Management Office)
On the 27th, ice was observed for the first time in this season at Tsuruke Pond in Johei (Tanseigawa-cho, Takayama City, Gifu Prefecture, 2702 meters above sea level).
It is four days slower than last year and one day faster than the average of the past decade.
According to the Norikura Skyline Administration Office, around 6:25 a.m., officials patrolling the road confirmed that the western side of Tsuruke Pond had about 2 mm thick ice.
The weather was sunny and the temperature was 3 degrees.
According to the Gifu Regional Weather Service, the lowest temperature in the prefecture was 9-5 degrees Celsius in 6 stables in Shokawa-cho, Gifu City.
