Yamagata City|Yamagata Shimbun
Yamagata City is planning to build a social capital development (PFI) system through the use of private funds, and a bidder for the children's play facility and the Nanumabara Koshin school building was decided, and an explanation of the facility was given at the Standing Committee of the City Council, which opened on 26th.
Image of a children's play facility newly established in Katatani, Yamagata City
The children's play facility is scheduled to be built on the north side of the northern part of Yamagata Kuchu in Katayaji District, and the site area is about 23400 square meters.
The building has a total floor area of about 3,000 square meters.
It has a semi-underground gymnasium, a cafe and a library corner.
It also has a universal design playground that allows children with disabilities to play outdoors, ensuring 300 parking spaces.
A review committee was held at the city hall on May 5th, and 13 shelter groups (Yamagata City) won the bid for 355 million yen, including design and preparation costs, maintenance and operation costs for 15 years.
Design and construction will begin in January next year and will be opened in March 2022.
Image of Nanumahara Elementary School
The school has over 900 students.
It is planned to be built on the north side of the current school building in Iizawa City, and the site area is approximately 25,000 square meters.
It is a three-story reinforced concrete building with a total floor area of 8580 square meters.
There are 30 classrooms, two pools, a steel gymnasium, and a children's club after school.
At the review committee on the 6th of this month, the Ichimura Corporation Group (Yamagata City), which consists of eight companies, sold it for 4512.1 million yen, including design, demolition of old school buildings, and maintenance and operation costs for 15 years.
It was designed and built in December and completed in October 22.
