The original manuscript before the suicide of Akutagawa was published for the first time.
The manuscript written by Ryunosuke Akutagawa, who was first published at the Tabata Bunshimura Memorial Hall.
The author Ryunosuke Akutagawa (1892-1927) published his essay "Shoku Bunshimura Memorial Hall" in Kita Ward, Tokyo, which he published in his last years of fighting literature with Junichiro Tanizaki.
It will be exhibited at the museum from October 1.
Although it was known that the manuscript was included in the whole collection, it was the first time that the manuscript was published publicly.
It is said that he wrote a few months before Akutagawa committed suicide, and the museum researcher, Mr. Sadai, said, "I can see Akutagawa, who was both mentally and physically weakened, facing serious problems in literature with a great determination."
A total of 12 essays on 200-character manuscript paper were published in the April 27 issue of "Ryushu Shunju."
